# File: specs/46-fix-migrate-project-auto-mode/feature.gherkin
#
# Generated from: specs/46-fix-migrate-project-auto-mode/requirements.md
# Issue: #46
# Type: Defect regression

@regression
Feature: migrate-project ignores unattended-mode
  The migrate-project skill previously skipped its interactive review gate
  when `.claude/unattended-mode` existed in the project directory.
  This was fixed by adding an explicit Unattended Mode section to SKILL.md
  that overrides the unattended-mode convention for this skill.

  # --- Bug Is Fixed ---

  @regression
  Scenario: Review gate is always interactive even with unattended-mode
    Given a project with `.claude/unattended-mode` present
    And the project has outdated steering docs with missing sections
    When `/migrate-project` runs and identifies changes to merge
    Then proposed changes are presented for review via AskUserQuestion
    And no files are modified until the user explicitly approves

  # --- Related Behavior Still Works ---

  @regression
  Scenario: Review gate works without unattended-mode
    Given a project without `.claude/unattended-mode`
    And the project has outdated steering docs with missing sections
    When `/migrate-project` runs and identifies changes to merge
    Then proposed changes are presented for review via AskUserQuestion
    And no files are modified until the user explicitly approves

  @regression
  Scenario: Other SDLC skills still respect unattended-mode
    Given a project with `.claude/unattended-mode` present
    When an SDLC skill with unattended-mode support runs (e.g., `/write-spec`)
    Then that skill's review gates are correctly skipped per the unattended-mode convention
